  "text": "This begs the question of the ultimate selective pressures responsible for maintaining a low internal P O 2 in insects. The Hetz-Bradley 'oxidative damage hypothesis' (see [CITATION_1] for discussion) is certainly worthy of consideration and, though defined in terms of the DGC, may be applicable sensu lato to continuous gas exchangers as well in light of our Oxygen guarding in termites findings. [CITATION_2] , however, reasonably limit their consideration of oxidative damage to the insect's somatic tissues.",
